    <div class="container">      
        <div class="content">
            <div class="summary-part">
                <h3>THE CHALLENGE</h3>
                <h4 class="program">I was asked to analyze Lucie Glaister;s website and make suggestions on how to improve the overall usability. Though the client had found success with e-commerce, she felt there was a lot of room for improvement. Specifically, she wanted users to spend more time on her website and make it easier for them to browse and look around as they would if they were in a physical location</h4>
                 <h4 class="program">The end result was a UX/UI redesign and adding a user profile feature. The user profile feature benefits users, many of which are repeat customers, by allowing them to select favorite products, share pages and products via social networks, and generally reduce the UX friction for her most valuable and loyal customers. The feature also benefits the company by allowing them to establish a customer relationship management (CRM) program via the collection of emails which can be leveraged with a newsletter, special offers, etc.. </h4>
                <h3>METHOD</h3>
                <H4 style="font-weight: bold">Usability testing</H4>
                <h4>Of course, I started with a much larger list of assumptions and possible improvements, but to ensure I was only spending time designing the most impactful, I tested these assumptions with usability tests with 3 people who matched the target market. (Slightly older 30-45 years old with a passion for high quality food)</h4>
                <H4 style="font-weight: bold">I identified these two specific use cases to focus the work: </H4>
                <h4>Purchase - Efficiently browse the retailers selection of premium, wine, chocolate and delicacies to find the perfect item for your tastes and/or needs </h4>
                <h4>Subscribe to newsletter - People with passion for premium food, looking for not only handmade high quality food, but they also want to buy products which are made from seasonal food. </h4>
            </h4>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="summary-card">
        <div class="summary-part">
            <h3><strong>Low-Fidelity and Mid-Fidelity Wireframes<strong></h3>
            <h4 style="font-weight: normal">First I sketched out a few ideas on paper, I selected and used what made the most sense and to get a good overview of the product I created Low-fidelity Wireframes. I designed a mobile first responsive web app and for that I choose 8 column grids. To create not  only Wireframes, but also <strong>Style Guide</strong> and prototypes I used <strong>Figma</strong></h3>
            
            <div  class="h-100 p-2 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-items-center">
